<task id="task_C837F916F8D7464798F96F0FC454B4A4">
  <title>Bookmark Onsite from Your Web Page</title>
  <shortdesc>The Onsite bookmarklet is a bookmark you add to your browser's
	 toolbar. The bookmark lets you enter Onsite directly from your web page. 
  </shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <othermeta name="solution" content="Target" />
      <othermeta name="topic" content="Advanced" />
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <taskbody>
    <context id="context_A865190EE6554E4BBDDB70C7FAD69387">
      <p>The Onsite bookmarklet places you into multiple campaign preview mode.
		  Choose a particular campaign to preview, or click "new campaign" to start
		  creating a new campaign. 
		</p>
      <p>After you save the Onsite Bookmarklet to your browser's bookmark bar,
		  you can enter Onsite mode from any page that has an mbox on it. Click the
		  bookmark, and your page refreshes in Onsite mode, allowing you to preview a
		  campaign or immediately create a new campaign or test. 
		</p>
      <p>To create a bookmarklet: 
		</p>
    </context>
    <steps id="steps_6BC9A18678E841EBA6469131F91A5B60">
      <step id="step_3F555365EC464E9C98C862426F08F033">
        <cmd>Click 
			 <uicontrol>Configuration</uicontrol> &gt; 
			 <uicontrol>Onsite</uicontrol> in the main navigation. 
		  </cmd>
      </step>
      <step id="step_B71A93B64B4349DCBA15FA7F7A41F7F8">
        <cmd>Follow the instructions to drag the bookmarklet link to your
			 browser's bookmarks toolbar. 
		  </cmd>
      </step>
      <step id="step_9011293DAE8340C1A129DE17E52895ED">
        <cmd>Navigate to your site and click the bookmarklet to enter Onsite. 
		  </cmd>
        <stepresult>
          <?xm-replace_text Step Result?>
        </stepresult>
      </step>
    </steps>
